io page along with a bio letter.\r\nWould you like to illustrate your own story? It’s perfectly find to send an illustrated story by yourself or a friend. If we like the story and the illustrations, we will publish them both. If we like the story but not the illustrations, we will find our own illustrator for your story. If we like the illustrations but not the story, we will contact you to see if you’d like to become a African Review illustrator. Remember to send copies of your artwork, not originals.\r\nPoetry\r\nWe at Africana Review prefer free-verse poems over rhyming poems. If you write rhyming poems, you should probably send it to a different publisher. At The Africana Review. We are seeking poetry that:\r\n•	Engages with the unfamiliar and jarring\r\n•	Articulates and provokes our starkest emotions\r\n•	Offers the reader unexpected modes of interaction\r\nPlease submit 3-5 poems not exceeding 1500 words, in one document.\r\nFlash Fiction\r\nAll flash fiction and flash nonfiction should be under 300 words.\r\nProse Fiction or Nonfiction\r\nWe are looking for prose that is arresting, that fearlessly disrupts the story on black teens and children. Stories that grips our throats. Stories that break our hearts. Stories that blows our mind. We want the unexpected, prose that extends the plight of boundaries blackness in form, language, or narrative. \r\nAll other forms: No more than 2 pieces not exceeding 5,000 words or twenty pages.\r\nGraphic Novels or Comics\r\nFor this type of submission, we request that you submit in .jpg, .tiff or .pdf format.\r\nQuery before sending in book reviews, interviews, and literary criticism. (editor@convenient.com) \r\nWhat Are Some Things That Are Not Allowed?\r\nWe are not looking for the stereotypical stories that have been rehashed repeatedly in the media when it comes to the black youth. We ask for the following subjects not be the main attribute of the protagonist:\r\n•	Gangster\r\n•	Drug dealer\r\n•	Teen parent\r\n•	Prisoner\r\nWe ask that if your story does have a common narrative in media (poverty, abuse, violence, prison, slavery, colonialism, racism), it cannot be the focus of the story. If it does, we suggest a different publisher.\r\nCan A Historical Figure Be a Protagonist?\r\nWe are not against historical figures in your stories, they just cannot be the protagonist. We are looking for fresh new protagonists that drive the story forward.\r\nCan The Protagonist Be Mixed Race Heritage?\r\nNo, the protagonist cannot be racially mixed and neither can the parents, if the protagonist has any. If you are sending a illustration, the protagonist must look visibly black. When we mean “visibly black,” we mean there can be no doubt of the character racial makeup to our readers. We will leave this up to you judge what is considered “visibly black.”\r\nWhat If The Protagonist Is Of Another Species?\r\nIf the protagonist is of another species, that is fine, however, if the species resembles human beings (like Superman for example), they must look “visibly black.”\r\nCan The Protagonist Be From Another Country Outside The United States?\r\nYes, they can be. We understand that the majority of black children reside outside the United States. We would love to hear stories from protagonist of different countries. Feel free to throw in your languages or use Pidgin English (provided with a glossary).\r\nWhat Stories Are You Looking For?\r\nHere at Africana Review we are looking for stories from these genres:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Action/Adventure</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Coming-of-Age</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Drama</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Fantasy</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Horror</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Mystery</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Psychological</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Tragedy</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Science fiction</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Slice of life</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Post-Apocalyptic</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n \r\nPayment \r\nAll contributors whose work is accepted for publication your work with remain on our site permanently. In addition, contributors of stories, poems, and book reviews are paid $50 each; illustrators are paid $40 per illustration.\r\n', 'Submissions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2107-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-26 02:02:34', '2014-10-26 02:02:34', '', 2107, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=2116', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
