(2143, 1, '2014-10-26 02:50:57', '2014-10-26 02:50:57', '<span class="afrikana">The Afrikana Review</span> is an online literary magazine featuring young Black protagonists, ages of 13-19, from Black writers who are often ignored in mainstream and independent markets. Founder Adlyn Morrison as teenager stopped reading fiction for many years until college. She believes if there were protagonists were created after herself and her experience, a loved of reading would have cultivated much earlier in life. Weary of the the lack of books Black teens could relate to, she sought to strengthen and expand the Black narrative in young adult fiction so that Black teens could see themselves as the default, rather than exaggerated tokens.\r\n\r\n<h1>MASTHEAD</h1>\r\nFOUNDER, ART DIRECTOR/WEB DESIGNER\r\nAdlyn Morrison\r\n\r\n', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2093-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-26 02:50:57', '2014-10-26 02:50:57', '', 2093, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=2143', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
