oubt of the character''s racial makeup to <strong>our readers or us at <span class="afrikana">Afrikana</span></strong>. We will leave this up to you judge what is considered “visibly Afrikan.” Please be aware that your ideal may not be others.\r\n\r\n<h2>What If The Protagonist Is Of Another Species?</h2>\r\nIf the protagonist is of another species, that is fine, however, if the species resembles human beings (like Superman for example), they must look “visibly Afrikan.”\r\n\r\n<h2>Can The Protagonist Be From Another Country Outside The United States?</h2>\r\nYes, they can. We understand that the majority of Black teens reside outside the United States. We would love to hear stories from protagonist of different countries. Feel free to sprinkle in your native language (provided with a glossary).\r\n \r\n<h2>Payment</h2>\r\nAll contributors whose work is accepted for publication your work with remain on our site permanently. In addition, contributors of stories, poems, and book reviews are paid $50 each; illustrators are paid $40 per illustration.', 'Submissions <i class="fa fa-envelope"></i>', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2107-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-28 22:53:24', '2014-10-28 22:53:24', '', 2107, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=2182', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
